Stakeholders in the justice sector have said that slow trial of criminal cases by prosecutors is a threat to the administration of justice system in the country. They identified low number of lawyers in the prosecuting agencies and shoddy investigation by security agencies as some of the problems facing justice delivery in the country. The stakeholders spoke at a webinar organised by The Probono Clearinghouse themed, “Access to Justice for Victims of Crime in Nigeria.” The head, Nigerian Mission of Avocats Sans Frontieres France, Angela Uwandu, lamented that access to justice had become expensive and inaccessible by many victims of crimes, especially in torture and extra judicial cases.